"Abstract A few months ago a fellow flight passenger and I conversed about our jobs. I mentioned some challenges regarding information warfare (IW). When we debarked, he said, “Thanks for keeping us safe.” He paused and then said, “Well, at least for keeping us ahead.” I was, in fact still am, struck by two things. He characterized the situation as a race. The stakes in this race are national sovereignty, economic stability, corporate survival and individual freedom."
